text: Oxydia cubana, the Cuban spanworm moth, is a species of geometrid moth in the family Geometridae. It is found in the Caribbean and North America. The MONA or Hodges number for Oxydia cubana is 6968. ==References== ==Further reading== * * * * * * * * * * Category:Ourapterygini Category:Moths described in 1906
